# React Router scroll position

When adding or changing routes in this SPA:

- Mount a single **`ScrollToTop`** component inside **`BrowserRouter`** (see `src/components/ScrollToTop.tsx`). It must use **`useLocation`** (`pathname` and **`hash`**). When there is **no hash**, scroll the window to the top. When there **is** a hash (e.g. in-page section on the home page), scroll the element with that **`id`** into view after the route content mounts (retry with **`requestAnimationFrame`** until found or cap attempts). Do **not** scroll to top on navigations that include a hash, or section links will land at the wrong scroll position.
- On app init, set **`window.history.scrollRestoration = "manual"`** once so the browser does not restore a stale scroll position on client navigations.
- For links to home sections, use **`Link`** with **`to={{ pathname: "/", hash: "produk" }}`** (hash without `#`), not the string **`"/#produk"`**, so React Router applies **`location.hash`** correctly. Shared definitions live in **`src/data/navLinks.ts`**.
- New top-level page components should not duplicate scroll logic unless there is a special case.
